LongDescription: The Kaliare Class is an ofshoot of the same program that created the Pskellon class corvette. Conflicting views on the naval acquisitions board split the design team in two. One was assigned to carry the program forward to meet the navies need for a small utility vessel, the other, to make a long range support weapons platform. The Kaliare is a result of the latter. Its designation as a light cruiser is perhaps flawed, as it will struggle to meet the demands of a dedicated frontline asset. However, making use of long range firepower, the Kaliare's are some of the deadliest ships in the cluster.
